Here's TUnit's lifecycle at each scope:

## 1. Before/After Every Test in a Class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // runs after each test
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 2. Once Before First / After Last Test in a Class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task OpenFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once before any test in this class
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after all tests in this class
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 3. Once Per Assembly (Before Any / After All Tests)

```csharp
public class WireMockHooks
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        await WireMockServer.StartAsync();
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        await WireMockServer.StopAsync();
    }
}
```

## 4. Once Per Entire Test Session (Global Start/End)

```csharp
public class GlobalSetup
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.MigrateAsync();
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.DropAsync();
    }
}
```

---

**Key points:**

| Scope | Attribute | Method must be |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| Test | `[Before(Test)]` / `[After(Test)]` | Instance |
| Class | `[Before(Class)]` / `[After(Class)]` | **Static** |
| Assembly | `[Before(Assembly)]` / `[After(Assembly)]` | **Static** |
| Session | `[Before(TestSession)]` / `[After(TestSession)]` | **Static** |

- All hooks can be `async Task` and accept an optional `CancellationToken`.
- `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` are the **global** variants — they fire for *every* test across the whole run (useful for cross-cutting concerns like logging), and can live in any class.
